Pour the boiling @water{250%ml} into a #saucepan{} over high heat and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2} until dissolved.

Add the @quinoa{120%g}, stir well and cover with a #lid{}. Lower the heat to medium and cook until the stock has been absorbed, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove from the heat and leave the quinoa to finish cooking in its own steam, another ~{10%minutes}.

In a #bowl{}, sprinkle half the @cajun spice mix{1/2} over the @chicken mini fillets{280%g}.

> Be careful it's spicy!

Season with @salt{} and drizzle on a splash of @oil{}. Rub the flavours into the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Roughly chop the @coriander{1 bunch}(stalks and all).

Halve the @avocado{1}, remove and discard the skin and stone. Chop into small chunks and pop into a large bowl.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Add the zest to avocado. Squeeze on half the lime juice and stir together gently.

Heat a drizzle of @oil in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, add the chicken pieces and brown, ~{2%minutes} each side.

Lower the heat to medium and cook the chicken, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every couple of minutes.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1} and @sweetcorn{326%g} in a #sieve{}.

Add these to the avocado and lime in the bowl.

When the quinoa is cooked add it to the avocado and bean mix. Stir together gently. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share between your #bowls{}. Top with the cajun spiced chicken. Finish with a sprinkling of coriander and a wedge of lime.